President Obama has nominated Judge Gershwin A. Drain to serve on the United States District Court for the Eastern District of Michigan. The President praised Judge Drain's commitment to fairness and judicial integrity, stating that his impressive legal career is a testament to the kind of judge he will be. Judge Drain has been a Judge on Michigan's Third Circuit Court since 1997, serving in both the civil and criminal divisions. Before that, he was a judge on the Recorder's Court for the City of Detroit and the 36th District Court for the City of Detroit. He also worked as an attorney in the Federal Defender Office for the Eastern District of Michigan and as counsel for the City of Detroit Department of Transportation. Judge Drain received his J.D. from the University of Michigan Law School and his B.S. from Western Michigan University.